# node-linker=hoisted · use npm-style flat node_modules layout.
#
# Why: pnpm's default `isolated` linker breaks Metro / Expo / React Native
# bundler-time tooling that does `require('yallist')`, `require('metro-runtime')`,
# `require('buffer')`, etc. from inside .pnpm-isolated package locations. Each
# whack-a-mole hoist (yallist, semver, getenv, metro*, buffer, ...) only
# patches the next failure. Switching to hoisted matches what npm/yarn classic
# produce — Expo's tooling assumes this layout. The trade-off is slower
# installs and more disk; for a build env that runs `pnpm install` once on
# EAS this is irrelevant.
#
# The yallist override in pnpm-workspace.yaml is still required to keep
# yallist@4 (CJS class) over yallist@5 (ESM-only).
node-linker=hoisted
